subject: Venture Pulse Daily Newsletter

bodies.content:
Curated VC Deals & Data .  Sign Up [http://venturepulse.org] |  Forward http://venturepulse.forwardtomyfriend.com/d-ndikjtdw-8B9F7A2A-hdlthyy-l-ji

The funding is female: 18 founders and VCs changing the tech landscape

In honor of International Women's Day, we've curated a list of 18 women making waves in the tech world. [ PitchBook ]

Airbnb announces travel partnership with France’s Station F startup campus

Station F today unveiled a new partnership with Airbnb, the latest Silicon Valley name to get involved with  the $265 million startup campus [http://venturebeat.com/2016/12/05/paris-station-f-to-open-in-april-2017-with-1000-startups-vcs-facebook-and-giant-expectations/] set to open later this spring in the heart of Paris.

During a tour that was followed by a press conference,  Airbnb cofounder Nathan Blecharczyk announced [https://medium.com/station-f/station-f-unveils-the-first-of-exclusive-perks-for-startups-airbnbs-travel-offer-for-4042bddd36dc#.rszzyrufa] that the company will provide travel vouchers for 3,000 entrepreneurs located at Station F. The value starts at $50, but there will be additional programs that allow some entrepreneurs to receive vouchers worth up to $2,000, as well as a $100 credit for anyone who becomes an Airbnb host. [ Venture Beat ]

For $600 in bitcoin, you can spam all the partners at Andreessen Horowitz

It’s a perfect storm of Silicon Valley buzzwords: Get your hustle on by pitching Andreessen Horowitz’s big-name partners using bitcoin, and create the future of money while you’re at it.

That’s the offer from the bitcoin startup 21, founded by Andreessen Horowitz partner Balaji Srinivasan.

Srinivasan, at one time tipped to  lead the US Food and Drug Administration [http://www.recode.net/2017/1/14/14276530/balaji-srinivasan-trump-fda-twitter-andreessen-horowitz], wrote about the rationale for the company’s “21 Lists” feature  on Medium [https://medium.com/@21/get-replies-from-vcs-and-ceos-with-21-lists-663f2a8d8b9e#.fu250hnjz]: “Almost every business eventually involves building lists of prospects and then contacting them,” he wrote. “Enterprise sales, recruiting, and fundraising are three activities in particular that fit this description. Corporations spend huge amounts of time and money in this broad area, but the whole process is still highly inefficient.”

Here are a selection of 21’s prices per list:

Andreessen Horowitz partners [https://21.co/a16z/]: $600 for 32 partners and top execs, like its head of marketing CEOs [https://21.co/ceos/]: $1,000 for 77 CEOs, mainly at biotech, bitcoin, and blockchain companies VCs [https://21.co/vcs/]: $1,100 for 39 VCs, including man of the moment  Jeremy Liew [https://qz.com/773328/a-vc-firms-simple-investment-thesis-follow-the-women/], who invested in Snapchat early                Get replies from VCs and CEOs with 21 Lists   Pay or donate to charity to contact many VIPs at once. Pay only if you get a response. Today we’re launching a new feature that makes it easy for businesses and individuals to rapidly get in touch with important people outside their social network, such as VCs, CEOs, angels, and founders.                News Roundtable! Liz Gannes & Ben Parr: Snap IPO, Trump tweets, fake news, Uber, drone cars

News Roundtable! Liz Gannes of 60dB and Ben Parr of Octane AI are in the studio to talk with Jason about the latest tech news. On tap: Snap's IPO timing, Uber moving forward, the Trump factor, Bitcoin, drone-bearing cars & 3D-printed houses & more.

FundersClub experiments with the full-service VC model at scale

Slowly disproving stereotypes, the online VC has established itself as a viable tool for tech finance. But while the model has made money for investors, the industry still faces perceptions of selling money for money’s sake, without much care for the nuanced entrepreneur-investor relationship.  FundersClub [https://fundersclub.com/], one of the earliest and most active online funds, is building out its own eight person engineering team to build hacks for its portfolio and experiment with what the full-service venture capital firm looks like at scale. [ Tech Crunch ]

Y Combinator is a waste of time—unless you do THIS [http://blog.close.io/mindset-yc-waste-of-time]

Is Y Combinator worth it? It’s funny: You can ask two totally different YC alumni that question and get two totally different answers, even if they both attended the same batch. How’s that possible? Why is it that, for some startups, Y Combinator makes a difference; while for others it makes all the difference? Trust me: It’s not coincidence, luck, or privilege. [ Close.io ]

Trump to Meet With Laurene Powell Jobs, Widow of Apple Co-Founder Steve Jobs

Laurene Powell Jobs, a prominent Silicon Valley philanthropist and widow of Apple (AAPL, -0.18%) [http://fortune.com/company/aapl] co-founder Steve Jobs, was scheduled to meet with President Donald Trump on Wednesday.

Powell Jobs, who was a Hillary Clinton donor during the 2016 presidential campaign, was slated to discuss immigration and education reform with the president, CNN  reported [http://www.cnn.com/2017/03/08/politics/donald-trump-laurene-powell-jobs/index.html], citing sources who claim to have knowledge of the meeting. [ Fortune ]

Millennials are paying thousands of dollars a month for maid service and instant friends in modern 'hacker houses'

Common [https://www.common.com/], a co-living startup, received almost 10,000 applications to fill its nine residences across three major US cities in 2016. The company is gearing up to rent hundreds more rooms this year. Open Door, founded in 2013, has established three co-living spaces in the Bay Area. The startup plans to expand from 40 bedrooms (with 140 more in the pipeline) to 1,000 rooms by the end of 2018. [ Business Insider ]

Looking for a hackathon? (http://angelhack.com/events)
AngelHack


** Announcing Our 10th Global Hackathon Series!
------------------------------------------------------------
It's our favorite time of year. The hackathon drought is officially over, 'cause it's SERIES TIME! And this year's Global Hackathon Series (http://angelhack.com/events) is a big one, in fact, it's our 10th one.

This year's theme: Commit To Your Code. We’re asking you to Commit To Your Code, and in turn commit to your project, a global ecosystem, yourself, your team, and your future.
http://angelhack.com/events
Yes, we're excited too! So here's what you do next:
1. Head over to angelhack.com/events.
2. Find your event and plug in the discount code: AngelNews for a discounted ticket (because we ❤️️ our newsletter subscribers!).
3. Share your excitement with one click (http://ctt.ec/cvLha) !

Current Lineup:

Nairobi (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-nairobi) , Novosibirisk (http://angelhack.io/) , Manipal (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-manipal) , Innopolis (http://angelhack.io/) , Los Angeles (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-los-angeles) , Mumbai (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-mumbai) , Sydney (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-sydney) , New Delhi (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-new-delhi) , Melbourne (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-melbourne) , San Francisco (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-san-francisco) , Abu Dhabi (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-abu-dhabi) , Brisbane (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-brisbane) , Barcelona (http://angelhack.com/angelhack-global-hackathon-series-barcelona) , Gaza

We'll keep you posted as new cities are added! Can't wait to see you all soon!

#AH10 is here.


** 🎥 Saw the camera crew at Global Demo Day?
------------------------------------------------------------
This is huge.

We had a documentary crew filming Silicon Valley week and Global Demo Day last year, which made us all feel like reality TV stars (but with less fake drama), and really put the spotlight on some of our amazing teams.

Well now, the trailer is out and the premiere has been announced.

If you're in the Austin, Texas area on March 11, RSVP (https://seedtoscaledocumentary.splashthat.com/) to check it out and walk the green carpet here.

AND WATCH THIS EPIC TRAILER (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MIZ0aKJh4gU) !

We'll keep you posted on more!
